<h3>Other</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Praefectus Magnus
        <ul>
            <li>Must use if you have it</li>
            <li>Not activated by money collection</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Storehouse
        <ul>
            <li>May not discard goods voluntarily</li>
            <li>If receiving goods beyond capacity (e.g. Prefect), may choose which to keep, but cannot choose to keep spaces empty</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>Game End</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Triggers:
        <ul>
            <li>Last personality card is purchased; or</li>
            <li>15th house is built</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Receive 7pt Concordia card</li>
    <li>Other players (teams) perform final turn</li>
    <li>Tie: owner, then closest recipient, of Praefectus Magnus</li>
</ul>

<h3>Salt</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Wild resource: may swap salt into any good at any time</li>
    <li>May not purchase salt</li>
    <li>Salt cities count toward:
        <ul>
            <li>Saturn (provinces)</li>
            <li>Jupiter (non-brick)</li>
            <li>Minverva (exactly one type of good)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Salt cities do <u>not</u> count toward Mercury (different types of goods) i.e. Salt neither counts as a 6th good nor a substitute</li>
</ul>
    
<h3>Forum Tiles</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Acquire when playing Tribute: 4+, 6+, 8+, 10+ to take from slots 1 / 2 / 3 / 4 or below</li>
    <li>Architect build action cannot be interrupted, but you <u>can</u> use a forum tile between moving and building</li>
    <li>(Venus) Divide card count equally or unequally and both partners may take a forum tile (or not)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Venus</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Actions of a card are also executed by partner</li>
    <li>Money is shared between partners; may not refuse the taking</li>
    <li><img src="~/lib/Images/Concordia/venus.png" style="width: 75px;" /> Max 14 points per card - solo game only, otherwise no limit</li>
</ul>
